Interface DenseVectorMixin<T extends DenseVectorMixin<T,U,V,W,Y>,U extends SparseVectorMixin<U,T,?,V,W,Y>,V extends DenseMatrixMixinOld<V,?,T,W,Y>,W,Y>

Type Parameters:
T - Type of this dense vector.
U - Type of equivalent sparse vector.
V - Type of matrix equivalent to T.
Y - Type (or wrapper of) an individual element in this vector.
All Superinterfaces:

      T cross(T b)
      Computes the vector cross product between two vectors.
      Parameters:
      b - Second vector in the cross product.
      Returns:
      The result of the vector cross product between this vector and b.
      Throws:
